name: Soccer Olympics
summary: Canadian soccer teams, both men's and women's, have been using drone technology and spying for years, according to sources. The Canadian women's team, in particular, has come under fire for using drones to gather intelligence on opponents during the 2024 Olympics. The scandal has overshadowed the team's victory in their opening match, with head coach Bev Priestman being suspended for the remainder of the Olympics. The team avoided an upset by rallying past New Zealand, but the spying allegations have cast a shadow over their win. The scandal has prompted calls for greater ethics education and has highlighted the complexities of the intersection between technology and sportsmanship in the context of the Olympics.

name: Skateboarding Olympics
summary: The Paris Olympics 2024 will feature skateboarding as one of its events. Skateboarding has only been included in the Olympics once before, in 2020, and its return to the games in 2024 is highly anticipated. The skateboarding competition will be divided into two disciplines: street and park. Street skateboarding involves performing tricks on obstacles that mimic urban street features, while park skateboarding is performed in a purpose-built concrete bowl with various ramps and obstacles. The top skateboarding stars from around the world will be competing in Paris, including Team USA's Cory Kennedy, Ishod Wair, and Nyjah Huston. The skateboarding competition will be held at the La Défense Arena, and it will be broadcast live around the world.
